        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 1:38PM MDT by NWS Boise ID</headline>
        <description>At 138 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Rough Mountain, or 45 miles southwest of Mountain Home. This
thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Areas of blowing dust reducing
visibilities. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Rough Mountain, Poison Creek Rec Site, and Doyle Mountain.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
